OL,6,F"I knew, when I looked out the bedroom
OL,7,Fwindow and saw the police ... walking
OL,8,Fdown the stairs that night, I'll
OL,9,Fnever, ever forget it," she said.
OL,11,FWhile Caitlin's mum was aware of her
OL,12,Fdaughter's drug problem and did all
OL,13,Fshe could to help her, she had no idea
OL,14,Fher daughter was in the sex trade and
OL,15,Fwas being exploited.
OL,17,FShe only found that out at her
OL,18,Fdaughter's wake.
